So. I’m putting five stars because I don’t want their rating to go down and maybe because my order was just a fluke, but it was a pretty bad experience. Red flag number one was that the tacos didn’t have a double tortilla (?!) so on the first bite, it just fell apart. The meat (carne asada) had a strange taste profile to it. It almost tasted a bit like curry. And it was cooked medium, which is not the normal for carne asada tacos. The guac on the side that I ordered was insanely salty. Like, SALTY. Everything was cold, I had to throw into my microwave. Wrong beverage order. Forgotten side. I’m so disappointed. My stomach was just not having it twenty five minutes after. I read so many great reviews and looked at great photos, so again, my order is probably a fluke, it happens, but I hope next time will be an experience that’s a thousand times better.

My wife placed a large order for my birthday using the menu on LaChula's website, were it stated that tacos were 4.00 each. i have the screen shot. She asked if they could call back and tell her the cost  of the order because the person taking the order could not answer at the moment. There was no call back. My wife went to pick up the food. And the bill was over 300.00$ she paid as it was a party and we had guest to feed. The next day questioning the bill she contacted the manager ( Megan) who was very rude and insisting the prices on the menu were changed. And the tacos were 9.75 more than double the cost!!! And refused any kind of compensation The fact is that the menu was not changed at the time of order, this is false advertising an illegal! I will be speaking with these people in person tomorrow and if nothing is still done I will be calling the better business bureau and the city and also my attorney not as a matter of $. This about treating customers with respect and doing good business and this place does neither!!

I use to eat at this location when it was a different more authentic Mexican place. I came back here after a couple years to find this diluted, gentrified place which I didn’t think of As bad, until I realized im not the kind of person they are trying to attract. I realized this but of how the person taking orders treated me. I am a latina, so I greeted him in Spanish with a smile and he responded in English with a very serious face. I didn’t think too much of it until I saw him take the next guests order (they happened to be a really handsome interracial gay couple) and  I was just surprised to see how big his smile was. He was so welcoming to most people except me and this other black woman. I was kind of surprised, but I still thought nothing of it until I accidentally dropped a glass bottle which shattered. I looked up at him to apologize as I was super embarrassed, and he didn’t even bother to look at me . He just rolled his eyes and looked away. I felt badly. I wont be going back to this place, they made me feel super unwelcome.
